##"China's top SARS ward" expert Tong Zhaohui: The current trend of severe cases has not decreased nucleic acid testing has introduced third-party | depth dialogue

Wechat Bqshenyidu

Features, Beijing Youth Daily, the official public number

Reporter / Tong Xiaoyu

Editor / Song Jianhua

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tong Zhaohui in consultation (first from the right)

What is the difference between new pneumonia and SARS? How difficult is the treatment? Young children and young people are not susceptible to infection? What are the characteristics of the susceptible population? Is it true that anti-aids drugs are effective in the clinical treatment of new pneumonia?

In response to a series of questions about COVID-19 treatment, on January 27, Beiqing once interviewed Tong Zhaohui, Deputy Director of Beijing Chaoyang Hospital and an expert in critically ill inhalers, who was taking part in the treatment of severe cases in Wuhan's front line of fighting against the epidemic.

On January 18, Tong Chaohui arrived in Wuhan with Professor Du Bin, Director of the intensive-care unit at the Peking Union Medical College Hospital, and Professor Qiu Haibo of the Zhongda Hospital affiliated to Southeast University, as aid experts, to Guide and take charge of the clinical treatment of critical patients in Wuhan.

As an SARS specialist, Tong Chaohui led 43 medical staff to set up the SARS ward in Chaoyang District Maternal and Child Health Hospital in 2003. He treated nearly 100 patients without any death and was known as "China's top SARS ward" .

Tong's days are now filled with seminars and rounds that continue until midnight to guide the treatment of critically ill and critically ill patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Intensive Care Unit at Golden Pond Hospital

Critically ill patients are older and more likely to have underlying diseases

Deep degree: Which hospitals did you go to after you went to Wuhan? What's the main job of the day?

Tong Chaohui: mainly treats the serious illness and the critical illness patient. At present, the serious patients in Wuhan are mainly treated in Jinyintan Hospital, Wuhan Military Hospital and Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University. My job is basically clinical, giving guidance to hospitals and doctors, pointing out any inaccuracies.

Deep degree: What problems are found in the clinical treatment?

Tong Chaohui: Cure a job to have no problem, but everybody is opposite this disease understanding, understanding is different, the assurance that acute aspiration failure is treated for instance is different also.

Deep degree: critically ill patients with what treatment?

Tong Chaohui: There is a clear definition for severe and critically ill patients. According to the criteria, there are severe and critically ill patients. The treatment policies for severe and critically ill patients are different, and the treatment is carried out in different ways, for example, non-invasive breathing machine, there are breathing machine, extracorporeal membrane lung and so on.

Deep degree: The young child or young person that everybody talks about is not easy to feel, accurate?

Tong Zhaohui: Whether Young Children and young people are not susceptible, it should be said that there is not enough evidence. Certainly can not say the child is susceptible, here can not say so, Shenzhen has the child to diagnose the case, now also has the young person to diagnose the case.

Deep one degree: so-called Susceptible Group, what kind of characteristics exist?

Tong Chaohui: The overall feeling is that, like the development of SARS in 2003, young people in their thirty will have more cases of infection, people in their sixty may be more affected now, and these people tend to have some underlying diseases, such as diabetes, high blood pressure, and often more serious illness.

Deep One degree: severe patients with the above-mentioned characteristics of the existence of these is it?

Tong Chaohui: Yes, older.

Deep One: will these critically ill patients now face some difficulties in treatment?

Tong Zhaohui: critically ill patients in fact mainly rely on breathing support, there are organ protection, corresponding to these things now we do are more professional. It should be said that we usually treat those viruses, pneumonia, acute respiratory syndrome, including SARS, the treatment strategy is the same.

DEPTH: Is the coverage of respiratory aids for critically ill patients now guaranteed?

Tong Chaohui: Now the quantity can be guaranteed.

Deep: Does breathing and intubation increase a doctor's risk of infection?

Tong Chaohui: compared with other patients with mild disease, the intubation process for critically ill and critically ill patients may need to be well protected. After being inserted, it is an airtight system. It should be said that the infection is not a big problem.

Deep degree: Wuhan surrounding areas of the treatment of critically ill patients? Are there any associated precautions or reporting measures?

Tong Chaohui: Every day there are reports, there will be serious and critically ill patients in the surrounding areas, but the critically ill patients had better be hospitalized on the spot, after all, the symptoms are serious, not good for patients to transfer.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of January 26, the Laboratory Department of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University had completed testing of nearly 1,500 samples

Signing with BGI, third-party testing

Deep once: Do you know Enough Hospital beds?

Tong Chaohui: for the serious cases, these problems have been adjusted, including the different hospitals treating the mild cases and the serious cases respectively, and now another new hospital is being organized. These are all positive measures to improve the current situation.

Once in a while: How are the supplies used for front line doctors, including ICU masks and protective clothing? Is it enough?

Tong Chaohui: The fixed-point Hospital of serious disease does not have a problem at present, but the problem may exist in the previous paragraph, now continue to try to solve.

Depth of one degree: whether there is difficult to detect, difficult to diagnose the situation? What caused it?

Tong Zhaohui: The main supply is not, a day can do the test is limited, there are problems in manpower. And I'm working on it.

Deep degree: Now that the kit has been put into use, what do you know about its application?

Tong Chaohui: Now as far as possible to test all the testing, including and BGI signed, let a third party intervention. We don't have enough people to do the tests, we need to take samples, and someone has to do all of that.

Deep degree: so the medical staff has been in short supply?

Tong Chaohui: Now the whole country is sending medical teams, it should be said that it will be fine.

Deep degree: for the preparation of the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, such as the establishment of these hospitals to alleviate the epidemic situation what role? Especially for the critical care patients you care about.

Tong Chaohui: A lot of beds will be added to treat these patients with coronavirus pneumonia, so it can alleviate the shortage of beds in other hospitals. Of course, critically ill patients may still need to be treated at designated hospitals.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The first-line rescue medical expert before entering the ward (the second from left is Tong Zhaohui) 

New-type pneumonia is more difficult to treat than SARS

Deep degree: You have participated in the prevention, control and treatment of SARS before, what are the similarities and differences between the two?

Tong Chaohui: There were more young and middle-aged SARS patients, most of them had underlying diseases, and there were more patients in their 50s and 60s. So the two are more difficult to treat than the new type of pneumonia, and the rate of intubation may be higher.

In addition, when SARS is fever, relatively acute onset, in the high fever phase will be infectious. The new pneumonia has an incubation period, during which it is contagious, and even some of them do not have a fever and do not appear to have obvious symptoms.

Deep degree: So the treatment of new pneumonia more difficult?

Tong Chaohui: Yes, 80% of new pneumonia is similar to SARS, 20% is different. What's different is that it's mutated, and it's much more difficult to treat clinically than SARS.

Deep degree: What Experience Does the prevention and control and clinical treatment of SARS have that new type pneumonia can draw lessons from?

Tong Chaohui: Sras includes the bird flu and a flu in the back. These are all viral pneumonia. The corresponding treatment strategies should be said to be similar, including the new type of pneumonia now. It should be said that they are all much the same. It is mainly respiratory support, ensuring that the patient is aspirated support, no lack of oxygen, including organ protection and other corresponding treatment. In fact, it's critical respiratory failure, which is what we do on a daily basis.

Deep One degree: Some experts have predicted that the number of infections may have an inflection point, through your clinical observation, do you have any forecast of the development of the epidemic?

Tong Chaohui: I dare not predict, because I am a clinician, mainly diagnosis and treatment of patients, the forecast is epidemiology and CDC (China Center for Disease Control and Prevention) experts, so they should be asked to answer.

Deep degree: Through your observation of the clinical situation, so far it seems that there is no decline in the trend of severe cases?

Tong Chaohui: There is no trend of decrease.

Effectiveness of AIDS drug blockers to be demonstrated

Deep once: Before this some infection disease expert says AIDS Drug Block medicine may be effective for the treatment of new pneumonia, how do you see?

Tong Chaohui: Now because are individual case, some is individual experience, did not do a few control studies, so it is difficult to say whether effective. Because we treat patients clinically with evidence, with evidence.

Second, the drug itself has no indications for the treatment of coronavirus, so I think it might have to be looked at, and it's not easy to say that it works.

Deep degree: What Prevention and control suggestion do you have to the common people?

Tong Chaohui: Oneself should notice, reduce to go as far as possible not ventilated, airtight environment, include advocate everybody to wear a mask now, with to the requirement of respiratory tract infection is same.

Deep One: What treatment and protection advice do you have for mild cases?

Tong Zhaohui: If there is no obvious symptoms of mild illness, nor Hypoxia, no respiratory symptoms, I think can be isolated at home. There are obvious symptoms, the severity of the illness, or to the hospital.
